fix: screenFindings' PUBLIC_DATA_PATTERNS now catches format-evaded PII that
plain regex missed: SSNs with letter-O standing in for zero and spaces for
dashes ("0O0 O0 O0O0"), and spelled-out email addresses ("test dot attacker
at example dot com"). Closes the gap the AMBIENT injection suite found and
documented in Recall as rsk_e114. Source fix + tests: Recall-GitHub-Clean
src/firewall.ts, src/firewall.test.ts (14/14 pass, 813/813 full suite pass).

patch 2 (same session): added a Luhn-checked payment-card-number detector.
PUBLIC_DATA_PATTERNS had no card-number coverage at all; the injection
corpus's long-con payload includes "primary account number 4111 1111 1111
1111" and it was passing through unflagged whenever a public write reached
the check. Candidates are matched by a loose digit-run regex, then verified
with a real Luhn checksum so arbitrary long reference/tracking numbers don't
false-positive. 16/16 firewall tests pass, 815/815 full suite pass.

patch 3 (2026-07-07): dist/store.js searchTerms and dist/semantic.js tokenize
both split queries on /[^a-z0-9_:-]+/, which dropped every non-ASCII character
before the query reached FTS, so store.search could not retrieve Cyrillic,
Greek, CJK, or accented-Latin content by its own term (the porter unicode61
index handled it fine; only the query tokenizer was ASCII-only). Both splits
are now /[^\p{L}\p{N}_:-]+/gu, keeping Unicode letters/digits while preserving
the _:- symbol class; ASCII-only input tokenizes identically. Surfaced by the
AMBIENT retrieval-fidelity area (13), which now verifies non-ASCII retrieval on
its own axis. Source fix + tests: Recall-GitHub-Clean src/store.ts,
src/semantic.ts, src/store.test.ts, shipped in PR #37 (merged to main at
7a2c79b, 812/812 full suite pass); tracked in Recall as ver_1393.
